##The return of the m-truck from Hubei

Wechat, boyangcongpeople

The function introduces, peels off the human shell, records the real sensible life. Presented by the in-depth Reporting Department of the Beijing News.

"Honestly, my greatest wish at that time was nothing but to find a place where I could stop and sleep for a little while, and I would be satisfied! "

Xiao Hongbing in the cab

By Beijing News reporter, Furong, Cao Wei

Edited by Liu Yue

The text is about 3,737 words long and takes about seven minutes to read

On the morning of the Lunar New Year Lantern Festival on February 8, Xiao Hongbing, a 50-year-old freight driver, finally got out of his M light truck in Hubei and ended his high-speed "vagrancy" .

He had a room to stay in. Coordinated by the Hanzhong traffic police and the Hanzhong North Service area, the service area provided him with a small room free of charge. The basic furnishings of only a bed, air conditioning and water heater were enough for Xiao Hongbing, after 20 days, I can finally take a hot bath.

Affected by the new crown pneumonia epidemic, January 23, the country's many high-speed entrance to implement traffic control, Xiao Hongbing's freight trip and return plan was disrupted. On Jan. 26, Xiao Hongbing and his flamboyant Hubei M truck were forced to drive aimlessly on the highway, which was hard to get off and down.

For the past 20 days, Xiao's bed has been the back seat of a light truck. He covered it with mattresses and bedding and parked it in a high-speed service area, "just sleeping it off. ".

In the video of Xiao's conversation with the traffic police in Hanzhong, he almost bursts into tears. "Honestly, my biggest wish in those days was to be nothing but to find a place where I could stop and sleep for a little while and I would be satisfied! "

Before the video was uploaded to the Internet, Xiao Hongbing was left with only a few hundred yuan in savings. On this day, he received more than 10,000 yuan of charity donations, as a future trip home.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Xiao Hongbing received love donations from netizens

The "delayed" journey home

The 4-meter-long light truck, with a red front and a body covered in dark green tarpaulin, is Xiao's main livelihood. He spent 20,000 yuan on the truck when he was "not making money" installing aluminum alloys in Jiangxi Province.

Short distance running does not earn much money, Xiao Hongbing try to choose to run long distance, the distance is at least six hundred km. Although a little harder, but the cost of long-distance running in terms of distance, each kilometer more than one to two dollars. He takes orders on a dedicated logistics platform, delivers the goods to their destination, and after unloading, waits there for the next order to go.

On January 7, Xiao Hongbing pulled a truck full of auto parts from Jingzhou, Hubei Province. Has passed through Zhejiang, Guizhou, Fujian and other places.

The last planned stop is Fuzhou, where, if all goes well, he can drive all day and all night to his home in Tianmen, Hubei Province. "The Spring Festival is a time for family reunions, and it's a long way to go to spend the New Year. ". It's an old rule in Xiao Hongbing's family.

Xiao Hongbing did not expect, after arriving in Fuzhou, a car of medical supplies "block" his way home.

"In Fuzhou, the navigation is all set, ready to go home, but just a customer said that the Spring Festival is coming to find a car, I hope I help, to see if a batch of goods to Sichuan. ". In the telephone, Xiao Hongbing learned that the goods to be sent is a batch of medical masks, the other side appears to be very anxious.

"I didn't know there was an outbreak at the time, so I didn't think too much about it and told my family that I wouldn't be able to go back this year. " A lot of time was spent on driving, and Xiao's information was lagging. Cell phones are used for navigation. He rarely watches the news. At the end of the day, he's often exhausted, trying to narrow his eyes and go to bed earlier than he would otherwise have. His family occasionally sent him information on the phone about the outbreak, but also did not arouse the attention of Xiao Hongbing.

On New Year's Eve, when he shipped his goods to Dazhou, Sichuan Province, he first noticed something strange. The high-speed access is blocked by a barrier to allow traffic in and out. Some of the places you can go, the police are wearing masks and protective suits. Xiao Hongbing had never seen such a battle before, and it made him uneasy.

At the Expressway junction in Dazhou, Sichuan Province, Xiao Hongbing chatted with staff while taking temperature readings. Only then did he know the details of the outbreak, while Hubei is a high-risk area.

Xiao Hongbing's van was inspected and disinfected. Photo courtesy of the interviewees

The Hubei M-car. It's got him in the crosshairs

Xiao Hongbing has not yet realized that his identity as a Hubei native and the Hubei M brand car have already involved him in the disturbance.

On the morning of the first day of the Lunar New Year, he was unloading goods in Pingcang county, Dazhou. Not far away, dozens of locals watched, murmuring in local dialects and pointing to the location of Hubei's M cars.

"I don't understand, I don't know what happened, " Xiao said. "I've unloaded goods in many places before, and I've never had people around and I've never seen anything like this, and I'm a little scared. ".

Someone in the crowd called the police, and within half an hour they were there.

During routine police questioning, Xiao pulled out all the high-speed receipts, one after the other in chronological order, to prove that he had not set foot in Hubei since he left Jingzhou on January 7.

Long time away from Hubei, no fever phenomenon. The police advised him to leave Dazhou as soon as possible.

The police left, Xiao Hongbing thought this proved that he did not "problem" . As he was leaving his local shop for dinner, his car was blocked again. "The local people stopped my car in front and behind with their tricycle. I tried to explain the situation to them, and they told me that cars in Hubei would not be allowed to stop. ". "Hurry, " the locals told Xiao

Xiao turned on the navigation on his mobile phone and set the destination to Jingzhou, Hubei Province, with the shortest route shown at 813 km. He re-opened the highway, as usual, he will never run back empty, "more than 800 kilometers, gas costs more than 1,000 yuan, the toll is about 500 yuan. ".

He hoped to pick up a load on his way home. An order came in from Shaanxi. He was going to Shaanxi to pull the cart of rice. But en route, the order was canceled because his profile listed Hubei Information.

Xiao Hongbing was worried. In the next order, he would first call the logistics company and ask, "I volunteered that I was a car from Hubei, and wanted to ask if it had any impact. " But as soon as the person at the other end of the phone heard that it was a car from Hubei, they even say, "No, no, no, no, no, no! "!

Staff members urged Xiao Hongbing on the phone: Now everyone is afraid of cars in Hubei and people in Hubei. Cars in Hubei can not get off the highway, and they certainly can not load goods.

Hands only with 2000 dollars, Xiao Hongbing dare not stay outside more, "no way, I accept the reality ready to run back empty. ".

Can't find the end of the journey, can only forward

But the journey home is not as easy as you might think.

Xiao Hongbing did not dare to tell his parents, who are in their 70s, about the situation along the way. He and his wife to discuss the phone, only to learn that the Tianmen villages, residential areas have been all closed management, all motor vehicles are not allowed to go on the road, even electric vehicles are not allowed to ride. No foreign vehicles will be allowed to stay.

Xiao Hongbing calls home 110 for advice. "They say if it's safe to be away from home, don't come back. Local medical resources are very tight and don't put pressure on the government or hospitals. They advised me to contact my local 110 and find a temporary place to settle down and come back when the epidemic is over.

Xiao Hongbing realized that he could not go home either.

Non-local towns do not allow non-local people to stay in the car, especially in Hubei. Quarantine points on the highway, staff also specifically told Xiao Hongbing: Hubei car "sensitive" , for safety considerations, not recommended under the high-speed.

On the Dazhou highway to Jingzhou, Xiao finds more and more high-speed service areas that won't let him stop. "I just keep driving, I can't stop. ".

"before navigation, there is a destination I also know how to go, but this navigation I do not know which destination to choose, I do not know where to go. ". He saw before him a road that had no end.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Xiao Hongbing and stand in front of the van talking on the phone. Photo from the official wechat account in Hanzhong

Service areas do not allow parking, meaning that Xiao Hongbing in the high-speed lost the possibility of solid sleep. He tried to get off the highway and stop for a short break on a country road, but a few minutes later a resident came by and said, "take the Hubei bus or you'll have to call the police. ".

When sleepy fast asleep, he pinched his legs and pulled his hair. I almost hit the guardrail a couple of times because I was tired. I was thinking, what am I going to do? I really didn't think I was going to make it.

After January 26, during a two-day, two-night trip on the highway, Xiao slept twice, less than two hours and 40 minutes at a time, both on high-speed emergency parking strips outside the service area.

Both Times, he was finally woken up by a traffic cop. Occupy the emergency parking zone, in accordance with the traffic law, need to Xiao Hongbing deduction of 6 points fine 200 yuan. But after understanding his situation, the traffic police did not punish, "they see me too tired, said this is a special case, let me drive away. ".

Xiao Hongbing had to drive on.

"I hope that when Hubei bus is back on the road, everyone will treat it as normal and accept it. "

Xiao calculated that since leaving Dazhou, Sichuan, lost the destination of that section of the road, the cost of fuel and transit costs spent more than 4,000 yuan.

Difficulties arrived, he asked the highway staff for help, the other side told him some central settlement of Hubei People Hotel, Xiao Hongbing hesitated, "if you want to stay, it is not a matter of two days, so do not know how much money to spend. "

He rarely stays in a hotel on long runs, usually sleeping in a high-speed service area for a few hours before running again. "As long as I find a place not to drive away, there is food, I sleep in the car does not matter, can adhere to down, but did not think can not stop. ".

When driving on the highway, the vehicles traveling with him are not many, and Xiao Hongbing paid attention in the gap between parking, "an average of every 20 minutes there will be a car passing. ". He once met a "fellow traveler" who knocked on the window of a car while Xiao Hongbing nodded off. The two men poured out their experiences along the way in their respective carriages and exchanged itineraries.

Xiao Hongbing's itinerary has not changed. His destination was still Jingzhou, and though he knew he could not make it, he only wished to get as close as he could, and he opened it inconspicuously, walking where he could, and winding where he could not, i don't know what direction I'm going in the back.

On Jan. 29, Xiao drove to a highway in Hanzhong, Shaanxi Province, and saw a sign that said "epidemic prevention and control are forbidden. " He found a more spacious spot, parked his car and slept.

By the time he was woken up by traffic police in Shaanxi, he had slept for nearly three hours, the longest sleep in days.

Traffic police did not urge him to leave, they took Xiao Hongbing away from the emergency parking zone. In the North Hanzhong Highway Service area, traffic police and service area responsible for communication, Xiao Hongbing's car can finally stop here.

In the cab, with only instant noodles, Xiao misses the taste of rice. On his first few days in Hanzhong's North Service area, he parked his Hubei Truck, first went to the supermarket to buy several boxes of self-heating Rice, 16 yuan a box, eat hey laugh, the amount is not enough, this just found a little expensive.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Food and water sent by Hanzhong traffic police to Xiao Hongbing. Photo from the official wechat account in Hanzhong

For the next ten days, he slept in his car. But the service area staff took his temperature and disinfected his car every day. Shaanxi local have a palm-sized bread, service area managers will come along with a few. The head of the traffic police also brought instant noodles and milk.

In Hanzhong, Shaanxi Province, temperatures drop to around minus one degree Celsius at night in the early spring, and Xiao starts his engine to fill the cab with hot air. But many times, "hot air" is also a luxury, blowing on for a while he will turn off, "afraid of fuel consumption.

On Feb. 8, the Lantern Festival, a video caught Xiao Hongbing talking to traffic police, and he almost burst into tears, "Honestly, my greatest wish at that time was nothing but to find a place where I could stop and sleep for a little while, and I would be satisfied! "

Before the video was uploaded to the Internet, Xiao Hongbing's body was left with more than 100 yuan in savings. On this day, he received more than 10,000 yuan of charity donations, as a future return to the home of the fare.

Even more surprising, the staff at the Hanzhong North Service area had arranged a room for him, free of charge. The bed, air conditioner and water heater are the only basic furnishings that Xiao Hongbing can afford.

"I carry goods for a living, and when the epidemic is over and the whole country is lifted, the recovery of Hubei is expected to lag far behind. I just hope our cars in Hubei will be treated and accepted as normal when they hit the road again."This is the only wish of Xiao Hongbing now.
